                                     FINAL REPORT

I implemented an advanced S3-based image storage system by creating a private Amazon S3 bucket with bucket-owner-enforced access and default encryption 
enabled to ensure secure data storage. Pre-signed URLs were configured to allow controlled, time-limited upload and download access 
without exposing the bucket publicly. 
CloudFront was integrated to efficiently serve product images globally with improved performance and caching. 
An S3 Object Lambda layer was used to dynamically transform images on request, such as generating thumbnails. 
Lifecycle policies were configured to automatically move objects to Intelligent-Tiering and Glacier storage classes for cost optimization, 
while S3 Inventory was enabled for tracking and auditing stored objects. Additionally,
a malware scanning mechanism was implemented using AWS Lambda with ClamAV to automatically scan new uploads and ensure only safe files are stored in the bucket.
